article.headline: CS Northridge 99, UC Davis 72
article.story: LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Ian Boylan scored 22 points and Calvin Chitwood added 15 off the bench as Cal State Northridge beat UC Davis 99-72 on Monday. It was Northridge's seventh win in nine games and the most points scored by the Matadors (16-11) all season. Playing his final game at home, Boylan, who ranks second all-time in scoring at the school and first in both 3-point shooting and steals, was 6-of-11 from the field, including 4-of-5 from 3-point range. He had eight assists and seven rebounds. The Matadors were sharp from the field, shooting 67.3 percent to UC Davis' 42.9 percent. Fowzi Abdelsamad led UC Davis (10-17) with 19 points, and Thomas Juillerat added 12. The Aggies started sluggishly and never recovered, making just two baskets in the first six minutes as Northridge opened a 19-6 lead. UC Davis had just two field goals in the first five minutes of the second half as Northridge went on a 12-6 run to stretch its lead to 20, extending that lead in the game's final minutes.
